@page "/"

<div class="container">
    <h2>Welcome to the Async vs Blocking Demo</h2>

    <p>
        This interactive tool demonstrates the differences between
        <strong>blocking (synchronous)</strong> and <strong>asynchronous</strong>
        execution in C# using Blazor WebAssembly.
    </p>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Why Does This Matter?</h3>
        <ul class="text-start">
            <li><strong>Blocking code</strong> pauses execution, making apps unresponsive.</li>
            <li><strong>Async code</strong> keeps applications responsive while waiting.</li>
            <li><strong>Parallel execution</strong> improves efficiency by running tasks concurrently.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>What You Can Do Here:</h3>
        <ul class="text-start">
            <li>Compare <strong>blocking</strong> vs <strong>async</strong> execution.</li>
            <li>Test <strong>parallel execution</strong> for better performance.</li>
            <li>Run <strong>API calls</strong> and store results in a database.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <a href="/async-demo">
        <button>Try the Async Demo</button>
    </a>
</div>